<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1913-11-12T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1913-11-12T00:00:00-05:00" n="1461" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d1461">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 702.9319/8.</note>
                        <head>
                            <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to
                                the <gloss type="to">American Chargé d’Affaires</gloss>.</hi>
                        </head>
                        <opener>
                            <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram.]</seg>
                        </opener>
                        <opener>
                            <dateline rendition="#right">
                                <placeName>
                                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Department of State</hi>, <lb/>
                                    <hi rend="italic">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1913-11-12">
                                    <hi rend="italic">November 12, 1913</hi></date>.</dateline>
                        </opener>
                        <p>Chinese Minister for Foreign Affairs desires following communicated
                            Government Panama: <quote rend="blockquote">
                                <p>Minister for Foreign Affairs requests recall of order revoking
                                    exequatur of Chinese Consul General Panama; at same time he will
                                    depute an official to replace Consul General Ou Yang.</p>
                            </quote>
                        </p>
                        <closer>
                            <signed>
                                <hi rend="smallcaps">Bryan</hi>.</signed>
                        </closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>